ject manager that follows strict protocols for software development\n- **Endor Labs Plugin**: New extension for enhanced functionality\n\n**How to Access Gemini 3:**\n```bash\n# Update to latest version\nbrew upgrade gemini-cli\n\n# Enable Preview Features in interactive mode\n/settings\n\n# Switch to Auto mode for Gemini 3\n/model\n```\n\n### **Release Schedule**\nAccording to the official documentation, Gemini CLI follows a **weekly release cadence**:\n- **Preview releases**: Every Tuesday at 23:59 UTC\n- **Stable releases**: Every Tuesday at 20:00 UTC (previous week's preview + bug fixes)\n- **Nightly builds**: Daily at 00:00 UTC\n\n### **Installation Methods**\n```bash\n# npm (global)\nnpm install -g @google/gemini-cli@latest\n\n# Homebrew (macOS/Linux)\nbrew install gemini-cli\n\n# Preview versions\nnpm install -g @google/gemini-cli@preview\n\n# Nightly builds\nnpm install -g @google/gemini-cli@nightly\n```\n\n### **Requirements**\n- Node.js version 20 or higher\n- macOS, Linux, or Windows\n\n## Recommendation\nFor actual February 2026 changelog updates, I recommend checking:\n1. **GitHub Releases**: https://github.com/google-gemini/gemini-cli/releases\n2. **Official documentation**: https://gitee.com/mirrors/Gemini-CLI\n3. **Keep the CLI updated**: Weekly releases mean new features arrive regularly\n\nWould you like me to search for more specific information about any particular feature or aspect of Gemini CLI?\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
