arallel editing\n  - Mermaid diagram markdown in chat\n  - New settings dashboard (usage tracking, models, team stats)\n  - PDF parsing via search\n  - Faster agent calls (parallel tool calling)\n  - Team management tools and API usage management\n\n**Cursor 0.50 & 2.1 Updates**\n- **Max Mode**: Enhanced AI capabilities with all top models, token-based pricing\n- **New Tab Model**: Multi-file intelligent suggestions and refactoring\n- **Background Agent (Preview)**: Multiple agents running in parallel with independent remote environments\n- **Improved Plan Mode**: Interactive interface for better planning\n- **Code Review**: Built-in AI code review in the editor\n- **Instant Grep**: Search codebase from sidebar with regex support\n\n### Looking Ahead to 2026:\n\nSeveral articles mention **Cursor version 2.4** planned for 2026 with anticipated features:\n\n- **Multi-agent Judging**: Automated code review capabilities\n- **Plan Mode**: Development planning with Mermaid flowchart generation\n- **Enhanced Composer Model**: Self-developed model with improved performance\n- **Multi-Agent Parallel Function**: Up to 8 agents working simultaneously on different tasks (frontend, backend, testing, etc.)\n- **Local Model Deployment**: Privacy-focused local hosting options\n\n### Official Resources:\n- **Official Changelog**: https://www.cursor.com/changelog\n- **Chinese Changelog**: https://www.cursor.com/cn/changelog\n\n**Note**: For actual February 2026 updates, you would need to check closer to that date as it's currently in the future. The information above is based on planned features mentioned in recent articles and available updates as of June 2025.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
